-- European Stocks Advance, Snapping Two Days of Declines; H&M Shares Retreat
-- B y   W i l l   H a d f i e l d
-- 2010-09-29T07:10:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-29/european-stocks-advance-snapping-two-days-of-declines-h-m-shares-retreat.html
European stocks advanced, snapping
two days of losses for the Stoxx Europe 600 Index. Hennes &
Mauritz AB fell after it reported third-quarter net income that
missed analysts’ estimates.  The benchmark Stoxx 600 added 0.4 percent to 263.39 at 8:10
a.m. in London, erasing yesterday’s 0.2 percent decline. H&M,
Europe’s second-largest clothing retailer, sank 5.2 percent.
Futures on the Standard & Poor’s 500 Index climbed 0.1 percent,
while the MSCI Asia Pacific Index increased 0.8 percent.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Will Hadfield at 
